Knicks Beat Timberwolves 93-89
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
	   NEW YORK (AP) -- Allan Houston made two free throws with 3.9 seconds left
after missing a pair moments earlier as the New York Knicks beat the Minnesota
Timberwolves 93-89 on Wednesday night. Latrell Sprewell scored 19 points and
Houston had 18 to lead five Knicks in double figures. Kurt Thomas had 16,
Patrick Ewing 15 and Charlie Ward 10. Garnett had 23 points and 13 rebounds to
lead Minnesota, which lost its fourth straight.
</P>
