<HEADLINE> U.Va. Sees Drop in Black Applicants  </HEADLINE>
   By KIA SHANT'E BREAUX Associated Press Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
	   CHARLOTTESVILLE, Va. (AP) -- Heated debate over the University of Virginia's
affirmative action programs is partly to blame for a 25 percent drop in the
number of black applicants, a university official said.
</P>
<P>
	   ``It's devastating,'' said Rick Turner, dean of the school's Office of
African-American Affairs.
</P>
<P>
	   The number of black applicants for this fall's freshman class fell to 961,
from 1,287 in 1999.
</P>
<P>
	   Turner said it is the largest single-year drop in black applicants since he
came to the university in 1988, and possibly the biggest since the school began
admitting blacks in the 1950s.
</P>
<P>
	   ``Any time you have a drop in enrollment there's no one reason, but it
doesn't take a rocket scientist to understand that one of the primary reasons is
because of the controversy we've been embroiled in over affirmative action,'' he
said.
</P>
<P>
	   The friction stems from last fall, when a special committee of the school's
governing body considered changing the way the race factors into admissions.
</P>
<P>
	   The university decided to drop a scoring system that gave an advantage to
some applicants for race and other factors, such as geographic location. But the
university still informally considers race among the many factors in determining
which students are admitted.
</P>
<P>
	   University spokeswoman Louise M. Dudley said while it is hard to pinpoint
one reason for the fewer black applicants, it is clear the affirmative action
debate played a role.
</P>
<P>
	   Overall undergraduate applications to the University of Virginia also
decreased by 16 percent this year. A total of 14,298 incoming freshmen applied,
compared with 17,090 last year.
</P>
<P>
	   Dudley said possible factors contributing to the overall drop include the
university's decline in the national rankings of top public universities, and
higher tuition for out-of-state students.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-02-17-00 0103 </TRAILER>
