<HEADLINE> Mighty Ducks 6, Flames 5, OT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    ANAHEIM, Calif. (AP) -- Fredrik Olausson tied it with a late power-play and
Oleg Tverdovsky won it in overtime as the Anaheim Mighty Ducks beat Calgary 6-5
Wednesday night, extending the Flames' winless streak to 10 games.
</P>
<P>
	   Steve Rucchin had two goals and an assist for the Ducks and Paul Kariya had
a goal and four assists. Kevin Haller ended a 41-game goal drought and Teemu
Selanne extended his point-scoring streak to 12 games with a pair of assists,
including his 700th NHL point.
</P>
<P>
	   Selanne, from Finland, reached the milestone in his 541st game and became
the third-fastest European-born player to get 700 points. Only Peter Stastny and
Jari Kurri accomplished the feat in fewer games.
</P>
<P>
	   Jason Weimer scored twice for the Flames, who lost for the fifth straight
time and eighth consecutive on the road despite rallying three times. Calgary
has lost four games in overtime during their winless streak after setting a
single-season mark with 10 victories in the extra session.
</P>
<P>
	   Clarke Wilm, Robyn Regehr and Jarome Iginla also scored for the Flames,
0-9-1 since winning Jan. 24 at Boston. The Flames are one away from tying the
franchise's longest unbeaten streak, set in 1985-86.
</P>
<P>
	   Olausson got the equalizer with six minutes left on a one-timer from 55 feet
that went through the skates of Calgary right wing Martin St. Louis and snuck
between Fred Brathwaite's pads.
</P>
<P>
	   Tverdovsky veered around defenseman Darryl Shannon and faked Brathwaite to
the ice before scoring his eighth goal.
</P>
<P>
	   Rucchin gave Anaheim a 4-3 lead with his second goal of the game and 13th
overall, tipping in Olausson's shot from the right point. The Ducks have a
power-play goal in nine straight games.
</P>
<P>
	   The Flames tied it for the third time just 33 seconds into the third. Weimer
got a pass in the left circle from Shannon and took a high wrist shot that
deflected off Guy Hebert's glove and over his shoulder.
</P>
<P>
	   Weimer then got his seventh goal from in front on a pass from Marc Savard
while Pavel Trnka was serving a tripping penalty.
</P>
<P>
	   Kariya put the Ducks ahead 3-2 at 10:15 of the second, converting Selanne's
pass from behind the net for his 35th goal.
</P>
<P>
	   But Iginla tied it 3-3 and extended his point-scoring streak to a
career-best eight games with his 16th goal at 17:02 of the second.
</P>
<P>
	   Regehr made it 2-2 at 5:04 of the second with a slap shot from the right
point.
</P>
</TEXT>
