<HEADLINE> Bulls' Benjamin Placed on IL  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    DEERFIELD, Ill. (AP) -- Chicago Bulls guard Corey Benjamin was placed on the
injured list Wednesday because of a sprained left ankle. He'll miss at least
five games.
</P>
<P>
	   Benjamin, the Bulls' first-round pick in 1998, is averaging 8.9 points and
2.3 rebounds in 29 games this season. He started nine games and has scored in
double-figures 14 times.
</P>
<P>
	   The Bulls made the move after trading Toni Kukoc to the Philadelphia 76ers.
In return, Chicago gets a No. 1 draft pick and John Starks from Golden State, as
well as Bruce Bowen from Philadelphia. The 76ers sent Larry Hughes and Billy
Owens to Golden State.
</P>
