<HEADLINE> U.S. Probes Newsprint Industry  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    WASHINGTON (AP) -- The Justice Department is investigating possible
antitrust violations within the newsprint industry.
</P>
<P>
	   "We have an open investigation into the possibility of anticompetitive
actions in the newsprint industry," Justice spokeswoman Jennifer Rose said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
	   The criminal investigation is being run by the antitrust division's
Cleveland office.
</P>
<P>
	   The Wall Street Journal said a federal grand jury in Cleveland has
subpoenaed more than two dozen Canadian newsprint salesmen as part of an inquiry
into newsprint price increases during 1994 and 1995.
