line up at a motor vehicles branch and take a number,'' he said tongue in cheek.
</P>
<P>
	   ``We've undertaken a lot of changes and I'm proud of those changes because
we've created a society and an economy in this province that is now
sustainable.''
</P>
<P>
	   His Conservative government will introduce a bill next month to expand the
types of surgeries for-profit doctors can do to allow for overnight patient
stays. Right now only day surgery procedures like cataracts are allowed outside
of public hospitals.
</P>
<P>
	   Klein wants to do it to reduce long waiting lists for procedures such as hip
replacements.
</P>
<P>
	   The work will be paid for by medicare and no one would get to jump ahead in
line by paying more.
</P>
