<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-17 23:54 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tulane 73, Alabama-Birmingham 69  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    BIRMINGHAM, Ala. (AP) -- Sarah Goree scored 19 points and Grace Daley had 17
as No. 20 Tulane beat Alabama-Birmingham 73-69 on Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
	   Janell Burse and Britt Themann each added 11 points for Tulane (22-3 11-3
Conference USA), which shot 61 percent to UAB's 39 percent in the first half.
</P>
<P>
	   Overall, Tulane shot 54 percent to UAB's 46 percent despite being outscored
in the second half, 40-33.
</P>
<P>
	   Mia Thrash led UAB with 20 points, and Holly Holland and Brandi Stallings
each added 12.
</P>
</TEXT>
